<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-02T20:32:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-02T20:32:00-05:00" n="590" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d590">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1265: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Trueblood</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                        Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-02T21:00:00-04:32">July 2, 1931—9
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:45 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>70. Paraguayan reply to second Bolivian note received and considered
                            cordial but unsatisfactory, hence instructions sent last night to the
                            Bolivian Minister at Asuncion to leave at once in that event are
                            effective. Argentine offer of mediation was withdrawn this
                            afternoon.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires and Santiago.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Trueblood</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>